    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001060/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """This course provides students with a comprehensive understanding of how embedded systems are specified, designed, and analysed through modelling. Students will study the principles and practices of modelling languages such as SysML and UML to represent both the architecture and behaviour of embedded systems.
Emphasis is placed on modelling requirements, defining system architectures, and describing dynamic behaviors using activity, sequence, and state machine diagrams. Through hands-on laboratory sessions, students will apply these methods using professional system-modelling tools to develop accurate and consistent system representations.
The course introduces concepts of Model-Driven Development (MDD) and Domain-Specific Modelling (DSM), highlighting how model transformation and automation improve the development of complex embedded systems. Attention is also given to reliability, safety, and fault-tolerance, enabling students to validate and verify high-integrity designs.
Upon completion, students will be able to construct and evaluate comprehensive system models, demonstrating the ability to integrate structural and behavioral aspects of embedded systems. The course equips students with analytical, design, and documentation skills essential for professional practice in embedded systems engineering and model-based design.
Enterprise Architect will be employed as the modelling tool for all lab sessions."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/agustin.yague%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/agustin.yague%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Embedded Systems Modelling"@es .

